          <title>BYU headed to Sweet 16 after 91-89 win over Wisconsin</title>
          <description><![CDATA[DENVER (ABC4 Sports) - For the first time in 14 years, the BYU basketball team is headed to the Sweet 16. Richie Saunders scored 25 points, while Trevin Knell added 14, as the Cougars held off a ferocious late run by Wisconsin to hold on for a 91-89 victory at Ball Arena in Denver.]]></description>
